postcontent:
PRICES LISTED BELOW

DESCRIPTION
Pistol Perfect is dedicated to a perfection level of clean, detail and protection to your firearm.
Guns need regular maintains for top performance and periodically the routine take down and clean is just not enough to keep your gun in premium condition that maintains its top performance and cosmetic appeal desired over time. We field strip and first air blast any loose particles and residue before wetting gun. This keeps residue from finding crevices and spaces to hide and build up as well as blasting away with no arasolized particles to create particles to still stick.  After thorough air blast to all parts a all surface safe degreaser is used to remove all chemical agents from gun metals and surfaces and hand cleaned free of all particles.
The gun is then given a very intensive detail cleaning to perfection as well barrel and all parts and surfaces. After, the gun is given application of frog lube liquid, with a light soft brushing and heated to 110 F and allowed for surface to absorb and then a light brush again prior to allowing to cool and retain protectant. A polishing cloth is then applied to again clean all surfaces as the heat allows absorbed residue to escape metal pores from friction of firing that heats gun and absorbs into metal and even further residue will be removed. Gun is then coated with premium Froglube Paste and again warmed to just heated (hot to touch) temp to to allow for a further deep absorption of protection into pores of surface while curing for an hour sealing protection into gun. A second polish cloth is used to polish the now smooth non greasy,  satin and condition felt surfaces and given light thin rub of liquid Froglube to friction points. The gun is assembled and given a detail with soft cloth by hand to get full luster look from gun, print free and unhandled shine. You will now have a pistol perfect clean that will not only protect and maintain gun but allows for smoother action and performance without greasy lubrications as the metal is given a deeper treatment that is notably smooth to touch and future standard cleaning is cut in half as simply wiping removes residue for many trips ahead to shoot.

This .30 Caliber American Eagle Luger is listed on the Bannerman sale records, verifying it as a genuine US Test Luger, and if you are a Luger Collector that needs no further explanation, suffice it to say this is one of the most desirable, and rare Lugers you would ever hope to see! The pistol is in good condition, the original finish is well-worn, with about 70% remaining – no pitting, but slight bits of freckling here and there. .10 Sale or Transfer of Regulated Firearms Without Approval. 

A. If a dealer or person does not receive a notification of a hold for an open disposition of a criminal proceeding or disapproval within the 7-day waiting period between submission of the application and a purchase, rental, or transfer, the dealer or person MAY SELL, rent, or transfer the regulated firearm if all applicable provisions of Public Safety Article, Title 5, Subtitle 1, Annotated Code of Maryland, have been complied with. The application to purchase or transfer a regulated firearm form shall be stamped "not disapproved" to show that action was taken by the State Police if a disapproval was not warranted.
